    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing configuration assignment in eth_get_dev_conf_raw_IF4p5\n\n### Summary\nThe `eth_get_dev_conf_raw_IF4p5` function in the ETHERNET transport layer was not properly assigning the received configuration data to `device->openair0_cfg`. This caused downstream functions to operate with uninitialized configuration data, leading to incorrect behavior in RRU initialization.\n\nAdditionally, both `eth_get_dev_conf_raw` and `eth_get_dev_conf_raw_IF4p5` had memory leaks where allocated memory was not freed in error paths.\n\nThis fix ensures that:\n1. Configuration data received in `eth_get_dev_conf_raw_IF4p5` is properly assigned to `device->openair0_cfg`\n2. Memory is properly freed in error cases for both configuration functions\n3. RRU initialization now works correctly with IF4p5 transport mode\n\n### Changes\n- `radio/ETHERNET/eth_raw.c`: \n  - Uncommented `device->openair0_cfg=(openair0_config_t *)(msg + MAC_HEADER_SIZE_BYTES);` in `eth_get_dev_conf_raw_IF4p5`\n  - Added `free(msg);` before exit calls in both `eth_get_dev_conf_raw` and `eth_get_dev_conf_raw_IF4p5` to fix memory leaks\n"
}